@startuml

class City {
  - name: String
  - inhabitants: int
  + getCityName(): String
  + getInhabitants(): int
}

class Attraction {
  - name: String
  - address: String
  + getAttractionName(): String
  + getAddress(): String
}

class GuidedTour {
  - name: String
  - duration: int
  - numberOfTours: int
  - maxVisitors: int
  + getTourName(): String
  + getDuration(): int
  + getNumberOfTours(): int
  + getMaxVisitors(): int
}

class Visitor {
  - name: String
  + getVisitorName(): String
}

class Guide {
  - name: String
  + getGuideName(): String
}

class Discount {
  - discountAmount: double
  + getDiscountAmount(): double
}

' Associations

City "1" -- "0..*" Attraction : has
Attraction "1" -- "1" GuidedTour : offers
GuidedTour "1" -- "0..*" Visitor : includes (max 20)
GuidedTour "1" -- "1" Guide : requires
Visitor "1" -- "0..*" Discount : may have (for specific tours)

@enduml

### Explanation:
- **City** contains multiple **Attractions**.
- Each **Attraction** is associated with one **GuidedTour**.
- A **GuidedTour** can include up to 20 **Visitors**.
- Each **GuidedTour** is led by one **Guide**.
- Some **Visitors** may have a **Discount** for specific **GuidedTours**.

